{
  "texts": [
    "A note on terminology: It is customary to call the basic set-up of a neural NLP (NNLP) system an architecture, and a fully trained, usable instance of a given architecture a model.",
    "In 2018, Hassan et al. (2018) describe a new machine translation architecture (derived from the transformer).",
    "According toGubelmann (2023, p.",
    "492), \"they argue that it has reached human parity.",
    "Läubli et al. (2018) have independently verified this claim and found that the architecture developed by these researchers does indeed deliver translations that are indistinguishable from translations delivered by professional human translators, though only if the quality of the translation is assessed on the sentence-and not on the document-level.\""
  ]
}